## 6. Install and Configure a Web Server

### Option A: Nginx (Recommended for Production)

#### 6.1 Install Nginx
```bash
sudo apt install -y nginx
```

#### 6.2 Start and Enable
```bash
sudo systemctl start nginx
sudo systemctl enable nginx
```

#### 6.3 Configure Server Block
```bash
sudo nvim /etc/nginx/sites-available/your-site
```
Example config:
```
server {
    listen 80;
    server_name yourdomain.com www.yourdomain.com;

    root /home/deploy/sites/REPO;
    index index.html;

    location / {
        try_files $uri $uri/ =404;
    }
}
```
Enable it:
```bash
sudo ln -s /etc/nginx/sites-available/your-site /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/
sudo nginx -t
sudo systemctl reload nginx
```

Visit:
```
http://YOUR_SERVER_IP
